    {
      "id": "abe31769_7338b84b",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/stats/PolicyStatsManager.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "Not sure if we need groupStat. As there can be only one subGroup for a PdpType (ex-drools). So, subgroupStats should be good enough or we can even rename that with groupStat.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3239,
        "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
        "username": "ramverma"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-11 21:59:57.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "68dda9b3_683b18ee",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/stats/PolicyStatsManager.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "The idea I had here is to keep it as a generic measurements class, where you can have a \"group\" start or global measurements, and then \"subgroup\" measurements where there are the details of the stats.   So, group and subgroups are used here in a more generic way, rather than the pdp groups and subgroups.   So the way that it will work is that on a PDP-D basis will have group stats with the totals, and subgroups of the form \"<controller, policy>\" pairs keeping the stats for those pairs.    I was thinking of arranging the subgroups on a per \"controller\" only basis, or \"policy\" only basis, but I thought the combination of both may be the more valuable to the user.   The When I finish the implementation, the group will map to the PdpStatistics top structure (PDP-D) and subgroups (<controller,policy>) will will map to the PdpEngineWorkerStatistics class of policy/models which is list contained by the PdpStatistics.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-11 22:42:19.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "abe31769_7338b84b",
      "unresolved": true
    },
